headline: Why TE Connectivity (TEL) Is Down 6.4% After Raising Guidance on AI-Driven Order Strength – And What's Next
summary: Earlier in January 2026, TE Connectivity reported first‑quarter fiscal 2026 results showing sales of about US$4,669 million and net income of US$750 million, with earnings per share from continuing operations rising to US$2.53 on a diluted basis. The company also highlighted record quarterly orders above US$5,000 million, raised its AI-related revenue outlook, and issued higher guidance supported by strong momentum across its Industrial and Transportation Solutions segments.
